def insert_after_character(string):
    return string.replace('A', 'AH')

# Test the function
print(insert_after_character('Hello Alice!'))  # Hello AHlice!
print(insert_after_character('The cat is on the mat.'))  # The cHat is on tHe mat.
print(insert_after_character(''))  # ''
